    <div class="article comment" id="cid-1583743">
      <p class="text">My mom's side of the family in Iowa has lefse every Christmas.  I always look forward to it.  We usually eat it with a little butter, white fish, and boiled potatoes.  Those that aren't so fond of the fish usually just eat butter &amp; cinnamon sugar.  It is truly a sentimental treat for our family.</p>
      <div class="footer meta">
