    <div class="article comment" id="cid-1584118">
      <p class="text">As a norwegian living in Norway it is very cool to read about this:)<br>But when you make them this small most will call it a "lompe". I Love lefse/lompe and eat it everyday. Here you have many different sorts and sizes. Some are made with spelt also.<br><br>most use them with sausage  and "brunost" brown goat cheese, but I love it with everything, pate and cucumber, mayo and shrimp and of course jam and cottage cheese (or creme fraiche)</p>
